<p>Hello there, I'd like to announce that the YATM Woodcraft module has been updated!</p>


<h3 class="bg0 fg1 ph3 pv2 mb3">Nodes</h3>
<div>
  <%= render_node.("yatm_woodcraft:sawmill") %>
  <%= render_node.("yatm_woodcraft:dust_bin") %>
  <%= render_node.("yatm_woodcraft:sawdust_block") %>
  <%= render_node.("yatm_woodcraft:packed_sawdust_block") %>
  <%= render_node.("yatm_woodcraft:wood_bark") %>
  <%= render_node.("yatm_woodcraft:wood_core") %>
  <%= render_node.("yatm_woodcraft:wood_panel") %>
</div>

<h3 class="bg0 fg1 ph3 pv2 mb3">Craft Items</h3>
<div>
  <%= render_craftitem.("yatm_woodcraft:sawdust") %>
</div>

<b>So what's new?</b>

<p>Not too many new things, the Sawmill has finally been implemented.</p>
<p>Right-click on it with any Tree, or Wood node to process it, for now every 4 blocks processed in this manner will yield 1 Sawdust.</p>
<p>And with that, Tree Bark and Tree Core nodes were added for the Sawmill, when processing a Tree node, it will split into 1 Core and 4 Barks (which are panel-like).</p>
<p>This was done to reflect that Tree blocks have 4 sides covered in bark.</p>
<p>Dust Bins can be placed adjacent to a Sawmill, this will collect any sawdust instead of dropping it at the feet of the player.</p>
<p>You may notice that Dust Bins can be interacted with by right clicking on them.</p>
<p>Right clicking with an empty hand will take any Sawdust from it.</p>
<p>Right clicking with any dust (Sawdust or Metal Dust) will place it in the bin.</p>
<p>And you read that right, Dust Bins will also accept Metal Dust, but for now just keep sawdust in it.</p>

